description.narrative: In 2021, with UNICEF support, Equatorial Guinea was better placed in strengthening the social protection system. Through UNICEF advocacy, the government included aspects of child-sensitivity and shock-responsiveness in their emergency response in Bata. UNICEF also supported on updating the law on establishing a social protection system, which is finalized and pending for approval. The social protection emergency interventions supported by UNICEF served as a model for the government and provided many hands-on opportunities for government official and decision-makers which proved to be effective. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/01/2022
